<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><span class="title">PROMINENT BOND TRADER DEPARTS MORGAN STANLEY <span class="divider">Â |Â </span></span><!-- end .title --> Glenn Hadden, a bond trader known for his enthusiastic Gatorade consumption, controversy and trading losses, left Morgan Stanley on Monday, <a href="//dealbook.nytimes.com/2014/01/06/prominent-bond-trader-leaves-morgan-stanley/"><b>Peter Eavis reports in DealBook.</b></a> Mr. Hadden was hired in 2011 to galvanize Morgan Stanleyâs fixed-income trading business, but his division posted losses of hundreds of millions of dollars, weakening his position at the firm.</p>
